  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "3-5. he walked in the first ways of his father David—He imitated the piety of his great ancestor in the early part of his reign before he made those unhappy lapses which dishonored his character.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and sought not unto Baalim—a term used for idols generally in contradistinction to the Lord God of his father.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
